	<h3>Striped </h3>
	<p>
		To get alternate row colors set a <code>.striped</code> class on the data table.
		IE7 and IE8 do not support the :nth-child selector, so a .striped class will need to be aded
		to alternate rows for those browsers.
	</p>
	<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;table class="datatable striped">...&lt;/table>
</pre>

	<h3>Hover</h3>
	<p>Adding a <code>.hover</code> class will enable a hover state on rows within the tbody.</p>
	<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;table class="datatable hover">...&lt;/table>
</pre>

	<h3>Condensed</h3>
	<p>
		The default responsive behavior of the data table is to decrease padding as the screen size decreases.
		To condense the table manually, add a <code>.condensed</code> class to the table.
	</p>
	<div class="outline example">

		<table class="datatable condensed">
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th></th>
					<th>First Name</th>
					<th>Last Name</th>
					<th class="loud">Username</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td>1</td>
					<td>Mark</td>
					<td>Otto</td>
					<td>motto</td>
				</tr>
